comments.name: PR10F
comments.text: L10F is a common non-polymorphic, PI-selected accessory mutation associated with reduced susceptibility to DRV, FPV, IDV, LPV, and NFV.

comments.name: PR20R
comments.text: K20R is a highly polymorphic PI-selected accessory mutation.

comments.name: IN138CFGHILMNPQRSVWY_-
comments.text: E138K/A/T are non-polymorphic mutations selected in patients receiving RAL, EVG and rarely DTG. They usually occur in combination with Q148 mutations. In combination with Q148 they cause high-level resistance to RAL and EVG and intermediate reductions in susceptibility to DTG and BIC. E138D is a polymorphism that occurs in 1% to 2% of viruses from INSTI-naive patients. It does not appear to be selected by INSTIs or to reduce INSTI susceptibility. E138G is an unusual mutation at this position.
